{
  "doc_id": "17638",
  "text": "Similar to the rat, the mouse PPC lies between primary somatosensory and visual cortices, spanning approximately 600µm anterior-to-posterior, and has distinguishable medial (mPPC), lateral (lPPC) and posterior (PtP) divisions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . To define precisely the boundaries between PPC and neighboring cortical regions, and to discern parietal sub-areas, we examined laminar architecture using Nissl staining, and chemoarchitectonic patterns using immunostaining against PV and M2AChRs.",
